name: NC Secretary of State
tweet: @cybersupportnet @NASSorg A3(2): Check your corporate records often. For businesses in NC – subscribe for free alerts when your company’s filings are updated. Business ID thieves will try to hijack a company’s legal existence by changing the registered agent or mailing address. #BizSchemeSOS

name: NC Secretary of State
tweet: @cybersupportnet @NASSorg A3(1): Keep a keen eye out for social engineering tactics. Phishing attacks will spoof email accounts to gain access to confidential data. Small businesses are the target of 50-75% of ransomware attacks, so remember – cybersecurity is everybody’s business. #BizSchemeSOS

name: NC Secretary of State
tweet: @NASSorg A2: Take care in what you share – innocuous personal information shared on social media can be used by crooks for social engineering purposes. If you get an unsolicited email or text asking you to click on a link to verify your account information – don’t click it! #BizSchemeSOS  https://t.co/UE7YHNERz3

name: NC Secretary of State
tweet: @cybersupportnet @NASSorg A1: Small businesses first need to be aware that they may be targets because they don’t have the anti-fraud resources of a big company. Consider all the different threats – internal and external – your business could face. What’s your cybersecurity plan? #BizSchemeSOS  https://t.co/78j0amZu1a
